The paper deals with the study of bounds for multi-prover games, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of forbidden subgraphs is a common technique in graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CG (computational geometry). The paper also discusses the density Hales-Jewett theorem, which is a result in combinatorics and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper explores the limitations of a new technique for proving exponential forbidden subgraph upper bounds, which could fall under cs.GT (computational game theory).
